{"type":"message-part","messageId":"705af50d-5683-4b73-91fb-4b704ba4dc33","role":"assistant","index":8,"part":{"type":"reasoning","text":"**Developing Backend Logic**\n\nI'm currently focused on building out the core backend functionality for the inconvo-app. My immediate next step is to integrate the express framework and set up the initial middleware to handle incoming requests and prepare for the Inconvo API integration.\n\n**Integrating Inconvo API**\n\nI'm now actively integrating the Inconvo API. The focus is on setting up the `/chat` endpoint to receive user messages, create new conversations via `inconvo.agents.conversations.create`, and then send those messages to Inconvo for a response, returning the result to the client.\n\n","state":"done"}}
{"type":"message-part","messageId":"705af50d-5683-4b73-91fb-4b704ba4dc33","role":"assistant","index":9,"part":{"type":"tool-todoWrite","toolCallId":"3KTX6qLsXqozS7zR","state":"output-available","input":{"todos":[{"id":"create-index-js","content":"Create /home/user/inconvo-app/index.js with Express server and Inconvo integration","status":"in-progress","priority":"high"},{"id":"implement-chat-route","content":"Implement POST /chat route with validation and Inconvo SDK calls","status":"pending","priority":"high"},{"id":"verify-server","content":"Verify server starts on port 3001","status":"pending","priority":"medium"}]},"output":{"success":true},"callProviderMetadata":{"vertex":{"thoughtSignature":""}}}}
